  "response": "No, you cannot see someone's status message if they have blocked you on WhatsApp. When someone blocks you on WhatsApp, you essentially become invisible to them on the platform. This means you won't see their:\n\n*   **Status updates:** Their photos, videos, and text updates in the \"Status\" section.\n*   **Profile picture:** Their profile picture will disappear.\n*   **Last seen/Online status:** You won't be able to see when they were last online.\n*   **Message delivery:** Messages you send to them will only show one check mark (sent from your device) and never a second check mark (delivered to their device).\n*   **Calls:** Your calls to them won't go through.\n\nIn short, blocking on WhatsApp is designed to completely restrict communication and information sharing between users.\n",
